The National Broadcasting Commission (NBC) has granted the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) operational licence to begin Direct Satellite Broadcasting (BSB) and Internet Protocol Television (IPTV). NBC’s Director General Balarabe Ilela presented the document to the NYSC Director General, Maj.-Gen. Shauibu Ibrahim, yesterday in Abuja.   Sylva: govt will unravel how toxic petrol was imported     Wike urged to join presidential race     Don’t remove Labour from Exclusive List, NLC warns   A statement by the NYSC Deputy Director of Press and Public Relations, Emeka Mgbemena, said the NBC director general stated that a radio licence for the corps was underway. The NBC DG said the licence for the digital satellite broadcast would give more voice to the scheme “to tell the NYSC story and its tremendous achievements to the whole world”. He said the NYSC, as one of the successful achievements of the Gen. Yakubu Gowon administration, has achieved its purpose of uniting the country in several ways and contributed immensely to national development.